The paper focuses on testing two different computing platforms for running deep networks as part of a humanoid robot software system. This involves tasks such as pedestrian detection using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques, which are commonly used in robotics. Additionally, the paper discusses benchmarking tasks and computational performance, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
